From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: experintellia <280144245+experintellia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 22:52:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 10/19] wasm: HTTP via browser fetch()

Replace the http_wasm.rs stubs with a fetch()-backed implementation.
The browser owns TLS/redirects/caching; requests are subject to CORS
(apps.testrun.org sends ACAO:*, so the webxdc apps list works).
JS futures are !Send, so the fetch runs in a spawn_local task and
reports back over a oneshot channel, like ws_tcp.
